headline_print_headline: Bursting the Bubble of the Billionaire

abstract: Days after Michael Bloomberg began taking steps to enter the 2020 race, Mr. Patrick’s conversations with top Democrats are the latest evidence of an unsettled presidential primary field.
snippet: Days after Michael Bloomberg began taking steps to enter the 2020 race, Mr. Patrick’s conversations with top Democrats are the latest evidence of an unsettled presidential primary field.
lead_paragraph: Former Gov. Deval Patrick of Massachusetts has told Joseph R. Biden Jr. and other Democratic officials that he is considering making a last-minute entry into the 2020 presidential race, according to three Democrats familiar with the conversations, the latest evidence of how unsettled the party’s primary is less than three months before the Iowa caucuses.

abstract: Bloomberg, Dimon and Gates call liberal tax ideas unfair. But excessive wealth is the real threat.
snippet: Bloomberg, Dimon and Gates call liberal tax ideas unfair. But excessive wealth is the real threat.
lead_paragraph: The billionaire class has begun unloading on Elizabeth Warren. A few days ago, Jamie Dimon of JPMorgan Chase — at just $1.6 billion in net worth, a comparative piker — said Senator Warren “vilifies successful people.” Then Bill Gates ($107 billion), in an onstage interview with The Times’s Andrew Ross Sorkin, mused about what his tax bill might be in a Warren presidency and left the door open to voting for Donald Trump should Democrats nominate Ms. Warren. And then Michael Bloomberg ($52 billion), who had previously criticized Ms. Warren as anti-corporate, signaled his intention to jump into the race, obviously out of concern at her rise.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg is the most recent former New York leader to mount or explore a presidential bid.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg is the most recent former New York leader to mount or explore a presidential bid.
lead_paragraph: It’s easy to get an inflated sense of self when you’re running New York City, with an avid press corps chronicling your every utterance and the city’s global prominence providing a bully pulpit on topics from international terrorism to President Trump’s immigration policy.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren’s tax proposals would significantly curb the gigantic fortunes of America’s richest families over time.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren’s tax proposals would significantly curb the gigantic fortunes of America’s richest families over time.
lead_paragraph: “Yes, billionaires will have to pay a little more,” Senator Elizabeth Warren said of the revised tax package she introduced recently, “six cents on each dollar.”

headline_main: Warren Would Take Billionaires Down a Few Billion Pegs
headline_print_headline: Fewer Billions for Billionaires Under Warren’s Tax Proposals

abstract: Appearing in Iowa with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, Bernie Sanders pushed his populist message and drew a contrast between his grass-roots support and Mr. Bloomberg’s billions.
snippet: Appearing in Iowa with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, Bernie Sanders pushed his populist message and drew a contrast between his grass-roots support and Mr. Bloomberg’s billions.
lead_paragraph: CORALVILLE, Iowa — Bernie Sanders on Saturday unleashed his most forceful rebuke yet of Michael R. Bloomberg’s potential presidential bid, warning the former mayor of New York that he would not be able to “buy this election” and chastising his plan to skip campaigning in the early states.
